      • toArray

        public int[] toArray(int[] array)
        Returns an int array containing all of the elements in this chromosome in proper sequence. If the chromosome fits in the specified array, it is returned therein. Otherwise, a new array is allocated with the length of this chromosome.
        Parameters:
        array - the array into which the elements of this chromosomes are to be stored, if it is big enough; otherwise, a new array is allocated for this purpose.
        Returns:
        an array containing the elements of this chromosome
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the given array is null

        3.0
